ABUJA –The Federal High Court of Nigeria, will on July 24, commence its 2023 annual vacation. A statement signed by Catherine Oby Christopher, Ph.D., Assistant Director of Information, Federal High Court of Nigeria, on Friday, hinted that the vacation will end onSeptember 15. The statement said the Chief Judge of the Federal High Court, Justice Honorable Justice John Terhemba Tsoho announced the vacation date in accordance with the provisions of Order 46, Rule 4 (d) of the Federal High Court (Civil Procedure) Rules 2019. “The Vacation will commence from Monday, the 24th day of July 2023 to Friday, the 15th day of September 2023” Dr Oby Christopher stated. The Court, according to the statement shall resume sitting on Monday, the 18th day of September, 2023. “This is in order for Hon. Judges to enjoy their well-deserved rest and to prepare for the challenges of the New Legal year,” the statement said. Consequently, the Litigating public will be at liberty to approach only the under-listed functional Courts in Abuja, Lagos and Port-Harcourt. The vacation Judges are: Abuja, Hon. Justice A. R. Mohammed, Hon. Justice O.A. Egwuatu. POLL For Lagos are, Hon. Justice I. N. Oweibo, Hon. Justice A. Aluko while Port- Harcourt has Hon. Justice A. T. Mohammed and Hon. Justice S.I. Mark. “The Chief Judge of the Federal High Court of Nigeria, Hon. Justice John Tsoho, wishes his fellow lordships a wonderful vacation in advance” the statement concluded.